@NODE WI_DATABASE "The database"

    The database.

    The database will contain all text for your photoalbum and references to all
    your pictures. Just to be complete I'll give a description of the fields in
    the database. 
 
    Key
      Key field, consists of a year, period-number and sort-number. These values
      are used throughout the program for different purposes like sorting, name
      generation etc...

    Text1
      Contains the first text or picturename.

    Type1
      Indicates if text1 contains text (T) or a picture reference (F).

    Text2
      Contains the second text or picturename.

    Type2
      Indicates if text2 contains text (T) or a picture reference (F).

    Text3
      Contains the third text or picturename.

    Type3
      Indicates if text3 contains text (T) or a picture reference (F).

    Type
      Indicates the type of the record. Every type will result in a different 
      layout. The sequence of the records in the HTML page is given in the
      the sort-number of the key of the record.


      Possible values are:

        0: Titel voor het jaar. De titel staat in text1 en komt in de menu pagina.
           Dient voor elk jaar aanwezig te zijn met sleutel YYYY0000.

        1: Toon text1 als <h1>, daaronder text2 als <h2> en eventueel daaronder nog
           text3. Zorgt voor de opbouw van de dagkeuze pagina's. Dient voor elke
           periode aanwezig te zijn met sleutel YYYYPP00. Bevat ook de hoofding die
           bovenaan de pagina's getoond wordt.

        A: Toon text1 alleen.
           +-------+
           |       |
           |   1   |
           |       |
           +-------+

        B: Toon text1 boven, text2 onder.
           +-------+
           |   1   |
           +-------+
           |   2   |
           +-------+

        C: Toon text1 links, text2 rechts.
           +---+---+
           |   |   |
           | 1 | 2 |
           |   |   |
           +---+---+

        D: Toon text1 linksboven, text2 linksonder en text3 rechts.
           +-------+
           |   1   |
           +---+---+
           | 2 | 3 |
           +---+---+

        E: Toon text1 links, text2 rechtsboven en text3 rechtsonder.
           +---+---+
           | 1 | 2 |
           +---+---+
           |   3   |
           +-------+

        F: Toon text1 linksboven, text2 rechtsboven en text3 onder.
           +---+---+
           |   | 2 |
           | 1 +---+
           |   | 3 |
           +---+---+

        G: Toon text1 boven, text2 rechtsonder en text3 linksonder.
           +---+---+
           | 1 |   |
           +---+ 3 |
           | 2 |   |
           +---+---+

  
@ENDNODE

@NODE WI_FORM "The form"

        The form.

        The form will allow you to enter all the required info in a user-friendly
        way. All the fields from the database are available on the form.

        Text has to be typed into the text fields, but a picturefile can be picked
        by pressing the appropriate button and choosing the file from within a
        file requester.

        At the bottom of the form is a row of buttons that allow you to Add a new
        record, Remove the current record, Duplicate the current record, Generate
        the web-site or Quit the program.
        
@ENDNODE

@NODE WI_PROGRAMS "The programfiles"

        The programs.

        Kiesfoto1.sbp
          This program is used to pick a picturefile for the text1 field

        Kiesfoto2.sbp
          This program is used to pick a picturefile for the text1 field

        Kiesfoto3.sbp
          This program is used to pick a picturefile for the text1 field

        Nieuwrecord.sbp
          This program will create a new blank record with a key value of your choice

        Quitprogram.sbp
          This program will ask for a confirmation and then quit Photoalbum Creator

        Stats.sbp
          This program will generate a statistics file for a given period

        Fotoalbum.sbp
          The big-one, this program will generate the full web-site
        
@ENDNODE
